{
  "stem": "10588.2",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was the only-- plus when they said, you know, the houses are yours, but the streets-- it still rings in my ears.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And one other experience that I had.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But that was not bad.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A bunch-- we were playing, winter, in the snow.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was a Polish little girl, [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Halinka. ?] I don't remember any longer her last name.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I-- the first name I remember, because we used to play sometimes.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My family never discriminated, you know, like, didn't tell me that I couldn't play with somebody.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were playing in the snow, and a bunch of kids walked by, and they threw snow at me.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So, and you know, said, again, derogatory things about Jewish.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So she stood up, and she said, she's not Jewish, she's my friend!",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I laughed and cried at the same time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because in other words, in order to be my friend, she had to deny that I'm Jewish, which-- she meant well.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She was a very good child.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But, you know, so-- it was the-- because of this here, plus that Orthodox Jews were involved-- most of the time at the synagogue, and involved in, in, in things which-- you know, volunteer charity work, and teaching.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So there was not much contact between the-- we had Polish friends, we had Jewish friends, but there was not that much contact.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
